    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-11-05T13:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-11-05T13:00:00-05:00" n="482"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d482">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">837.00/4339: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Cuba</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Welles</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Habana</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-11-05T13:00:00-05:00"
                            >November 5, 1933—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 2:30 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>428. The referendum of the university students taken in an orderly manner
                    yesterday afternoon showed an overwhelming majority opposed to the continuation
                    of student activities in the government and a similar majority against the
                    present Student Directorate.</p>
                <p>In order to attempt to prevent a vote of censure by the meeting of the student
                    delegates the Student Directorate last night formally dissolved. Some of the
                    members at once announced that they would remain in the Palace “as individuals”
                    to “advise” Grau.</p>
                <p>The dissolution of the Directorate and the vote of the university students
                    officially deprives Grau San Martín and his government of the apparent support
                    of the university which he had made it appear he possessed.</p>
                <p>The relations between Batista and Grau are increasingly strained.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Welles</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
